  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Department of Veterans Affairs contract obligations for FY2026 to date total $51.1B. Award activity comprises 54,736 awards with an average award size of $933K. Obligations fell 34.8% year over year. Historical fiscal-year totals show a rise from $47.7B in FY21 to $78.3B in FY25 before the current FY26 to date total of $51.1B. The largest spending categories in FY2026 to date include Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers at $14.4B, Pharmaceutical Preparation Manufacturing at $9.9B, and Offices of Physicians (except Mental Health Specialists) at $7.6B. Top vendors for FY2026 to date include MCKESSON CORPORATION with $9.6B, TRIWEST HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE CORP with $7.9B, and OPTUM PUBLIC SECTOR SOLUTIONS, INC. with $6.6B. The FY2026 to date snapshot reflects both medical and IT-related contracting, with Computer Systems Design Services at $2.9B and Software Publishers at $580M among the top NAICS categories.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has VA contract spending changed year over year?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 34.8% year over year. After increasing from $47.7B in FY21 to $78.3B in FY25, FY2026 to date obligations are $51.1B. The FY2026 to date total is a partial fiscal-year figure. Award volume for the period is 54,736 awards with an average award size of $933K."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What are VA's largest contract categories and vendors in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "Top NAICS categories by obligations are Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers at $14.4B, Pharmaceutical Preparation Manufacturing at $9.9B, and Offices of Physicians (except Mental Health Specialists) at $7.6B. Leading vendors are MCKESSON CORPORATION with $9.6B, TRIWEST HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE CORP with $7.9B, and OPTUM PUBLIC SECTOR SOLUTIONS, INC. with $6.6B. IT-related categories include Computer Systems Design Services at $2.9B and Software Publishers at $580M."
      }
    ]
